wikipedia_page.main: Alannah Stephenson (born 4 December 1996) is an Irish female badminton player. In 2012, she became the runner-up of Fyffes Irish Future Series 2012 in women's doubles event with her partner Rachael Darragh. In 2014, she participated at the Commonwealth Games in Glasgow, Scotland.

response: Rachael Darragh (born 24 September 1997) is an Irish badminton player who trained at the Raphoe badminton club. She won the girls' singles bronze medal at the 2012 UK School Games held in London. At the same year, she became the runner-up of 2012 Fyffes Irish Future Series in the women's doubles event with her partner Alannah Stephenson. Darragh competed at the 2015 Baku and 2019 Minsk European Games, also represented Northern Ireland at the 2018 Commonwealth Games in Gold Coast, Australia.
